    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-24T09:18:19+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-24T09:18:19+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-23T23:48:19Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-23T23:48:19Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure is building over South Australia, with the associated high centre expected to lie over the Bight during Friday and Saturday. The high will move north over South Australia on Sunday, with a trough to build over the west of the State later Sunday ahead of a cold front to move over the Bight late Monday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-24T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-23T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds southeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures between 14 and 18.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 2:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 4 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-25T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-26T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-24T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-25T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 2 and 5 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta, near zero chance elsewhere. Patches of morning frost west of Leigh Creek. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to southeasterly during the day then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 2 and 5 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Leigh Creek. Patches of morning frost west of Leigh Creek. Light winds becoming north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
